Describe a good friend who is important to you.
- who he/she is
- how/where you got to know him/her
- how long have you known each other
- and explain why he/she is important to you

I’d like to talk about my best friend Linh, who is a very important person in my life.

We first met when we were in secondary school, and we’ve known each other for several years now. Over time, we became very close because we shared a lot of experiences together, both good and bad.

Linh is a very supportive and honest person. She’s always there for me whenever I need someone to talk to. At the same time, she gives me honest advice, even when it’s not easy to hear. For example, before an important speaking contest, she helped me practice and encouraged me, which made me feel much more confident.

Another thing I like about her is her positive personality. She is cheerful and has a great sense of humor, so she can easily cheer me up when I feel stressed or tired.

I think Linh is very important to me because she understands me well and always supports me. Having a friend like her makes my life better, and I feel really lucky to have her.
